{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# CHANGELOG.md: git-cliff, prepend-scoped generate-then-curate from conventional commits\n\n## Why\n\nNo user-facing changelog exists: `docs/release-notes.md` is the agent-facing contract-change log, and GitHub Releases notes are auto-generated. Across nine surveyed Python tools, towncrier (pip/pytest) solves a many-contributor merge-conflict problem rebar doesn't have; ruff/uv generate from PR labels (needs a PR workflow rebar doesn't have); git-cliff converts the conventional-commit discipline rebar already pays for into a changelog. Keep-a-Changelog is the convergent shape (rich's CHANGELOG.md is the exemplar). Rejected alternatives — towncrier (double-entry ceremony), PR-label generation (no PRs), GitHub-Releases-only (no in-repo artifact) — recorded in cliff.toml header comments.\n\n## What\n\n- Add `cliff.toml`. Keys under their proper sections (a top-level key is silently ignored): `[git] conventional_commits = true`, `filter_unconventional = false`, plus a catch-all commit parser so mixed-history commits are kept. The normative `commit_parsers` mapping (each line individually grep-provable in the AC): `feat` → \"Added\"; `fix` → \"Fixed\"; breaking (`!`/BREAKING CHANGE) → \"Breaking\" (own group, listed first); `perf` → \"Changed\"; `refactor` → \"Changed\"; `docs` → \"Documentation\"; skipped: `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `test`.\n- **Pin the tool with an explicit version variable:** Makefile gains `GIT_CLIFF_VERSION := <exact 2.x pin chosen at execution>` and a `make changelog` target that (a) errors clearly if `git-cliff` is missing or its `--version` mismatches the pin, and (b) errors if `VERSION` is not supplied. Install path documented in docs/releasing.md as `pipx install git-cliff==<pin>` (standalone Rust binary; NOT a pyproject dev extra).\n- **Invocation interface (resolves the missing-parameter finding):** `make changelog VERSION=vX.Y.Z` → runs exactly `git cliff --unreleased --tag $(VERSION) --prepend CHANGELOG.md`. Full-file regeneration is forbidden after initial generation: the initial run (once, back through v0.1.0; ledger quality accepted for history) is executed manually and documented as one-time; thereafter only the prepend-scoped target is sanctioned, so committed hand-curated sections are never touched. The maintainer hand-curates the newly prepended section before tagging.\n- Include `## [Unreleased]` and the compare-link block (rich pattern).\n- `docs/releasing.md` gains the step: `make changelog VERSION=vX.Y.Z` → curate the top section (~5 min) → commit → tag; plus the pin + install line. Dial position recorded there: generate-then-edit (pure-generated rejected as ledger-like; mypy-style prose rejected as unsustainable solo).\n- **Repoint `[project.urls]` Changelog** (required edit; currently `docs/release-notes.md`, pyproject.toml:78) → `https://github.com/navapbc/rebar/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md`.\n- Pointer line at the top of `docs/release-notes.md`: \"User-facing changelog: CHANGELOG.md; this file tracks agent-visible contract changes\" (the epic's cross-link AC, owned here).\n- Known consumer, acknowledged: `src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py:310` classifies CHANGELOG-touching diffs as a hard-to-reverse surface, so curation commits score higher review impact — accepted; no code change.\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: `cliff.toml`, `CHANGELOG.md`, Makefile (`GIT_CLIFF_VERSION` + `changelog` target), `docs/releasing.md` step, pyproject urls repoint, release-notes pointer line.\nOUT: towncrier/news fragments; changing commit conventions; back-editing published GitHub Releases; the auto-generated GitHub Releases notes (complementary, unchanged); any change to workflow_ops.py.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` exists — prove: `grep -c \"^## \\[\" CHANGELOG.md` ≥ 8 and `grep -q \"\\[Unreleased\\]\" CHANGELOG.md` and a compare-link block at the bottom (`grep -q \"compare/\" CHANGELOG.md`).\n- [ ] `cliff.toml` normative mapping — prove, each individually: `grep -q \"feat\" cliff.toml && grep -q \"Added\" cliff.toml`; `grep -q \"fix\" cliff.toml && grep -q \"Fixed\" cliff.toml`; `grep -qi \"breaking\" cliff.toml`; `grep -q \"refactor\" cliff.toml`; `grep -q \"Documentation\" cliff.toml`; skips present: `grep -q \"chore\" cliff.toml`; structure: `grep -A3 \"\\[git\\]\" cliff.toml | grep -q \"filter_unconventional = false\"`; catch-all parser present (a trailing `message = \".*\"`-style rule) — prove: `grep -q '\"\\.\\*\"' cliff.toml`; header comments record the rejected alternatives — prove: `grep -qi \"towncrier\" cliff.toml`.\n- [ ] Makefile interface — prove: `grep -q \"GIT_CLIFF_VERSION\" Makefile`; `grep -q -- \"--unreleased\" Makefile`; `grep -q -- \"--prepend\" Makefile`; `grep -q \"VERSION\" Makefile` with a guard that errors when unset (`grep -qi \"VERSION is required\\|VERSION not set\" Makefile`); no bare full-regen invocation in the target.\n- [ ] Idempotence of the sanctioned path: running `make changelog VERSION=<current>` twice with no new commits produces no second diff.\n- [ ] docs/releasing.md — prove: `grep -q \"git-cliff==\" docs/releasing.md` (the literal pinned install spec) and `grep -q \"make changelog\" docs/releasing.md`.\n- [ ] URL repoint + pointer — prove: `grep \"^Changelog\" pyproject.toml | grep -q \"CHANGELOG.md\"`; `head -5 docs/release-notes.md | grep -q \"CHANGELOG.md\"`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783644034311529001,"uuid":"5a6f0bb1-b42e-448d-a18b-3f7f9dacc7d1"}